gn:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">4.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Staff at Heathrow, Gatwick and London City airports have been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">equipped with new technology to better serve customers with information and rebooking services during times of disruption. The introduction of mobile device technology in airport terminals will result in a superior and speedier resolution for the customer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in times of disruption. This technology will also ensure colleagues have up-to-date operational flight information, and will be empowered to answer customer queries efficiently, both during normal operations and in times of disruption</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">4.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A review of customer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> hotel booking and allocation processes has been undertaken to make it more efficient. The Hotel Provision Project has been set up in partnership with Heathrow Airport Ltd (HAL) and the British Hotel Reservation Centre (BHRC), to "share inventory" about ho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tel rooms during disruption and to identify suitable facilities around Heathrow.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-fam